CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 13, 1961, pg. 18, reads: "Human Rights Parley - Among the principals who sparked the success of the seventh annual Human Rights Dinner, sponsored by the Pittsburgh branch NAACP at the Hotel Penn Sheraton on Monday night, enjoying a 'tete a tete,' are: Frank D. Reeves, left front, special assistant to President Kennedy, who was the featured speaker; Branch Rickey, right front, who received the 'Human Rights Award' for his distinctive and unselfish achievements in the field of race relations; Roland M. Sawyer, seated, center, who served as toastmaster; Congressman William Moorehead, standing, left and Atty. Byrd Brown, standing, right, who is president of the local NAACP branch. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Featured guests at NAACP Human Rights dinner, seated from left: special assistant to President Kennedy Frank D. Reeves, Roland M. Sawyer, Branch Rickey seated; standing: Congressman William Moorehead and Pittsburgh NAACP president Byrd Brown, in Hotel Penn Sheraton
